name: Earth, FKA - Gaia, Terra, Tellus
description: Earth—our home planet—is the only place we know of so far that’s inhabited by living things. It's also the only planet in our solar system with liquid water on the surface.
atmosphere: A dry atmosphere is composed of 78.084% nitrogen, 20.946% oxygen, 0.934% argon, and trace amounts of carbon dioxide and other gaseous molecules. Water vapor content varies between 0.01% and 4% but averages about 1%. Clouds cover around two thirds of Earth's surface, more so over oceans than land.

name: 55 Cancri e
description: A molten surface planet with sparkling silicate skies. Approximately 8 times heavier than Earth with twice the diameter

name: Kepler 22b
atmosphere: volatile composition with a liquid or gaseous outer shell

name: Upsilon Andromedae b (formerly Saffar)
description: A giant planet composed mainly of gas, it has no solid surface.
atmosphere: clouds of silicates and iron in the upper atmosphere.

name: HD 80606 b
description: HD 80606 b has the most eccentric orbit, and as one scientist put it, 'wears its heart on its sleeve,' with storms, rotation, atmospheric heating, and a volatile orbit all plainly visible. Its mass is 4.38 Jupiters, it takes 111.4 days to complete one orbit of its star, and is 0.4565 AU from its star.
atmosphere: gassy and has a very eccentric orbit.

name: HD 189733 b
description: The planet’s cobalt blue colour comes from a hazy, blow-torched atmosphere containing clouds laced with glass. Howling winds send the storming glass sideways at 5,400 mph (2km/s), whipping all in a sickening spiral.
